[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hooe crash: Four held after people flee head-on crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Four people have been arrested after a head-on crash in East Sussex left a driver with serious injuries.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Two vehicles collided just after 22:30 BST on Saturday near the Lamb Pub on the A259 at Hooe, police said.
A driver was trapped for two hours before he was cut free and taken to hospital with serious injuries.
The occupants of the other car fled, leading to a police dog and helicopter search of open land nearby.
The road was closed for several hours while forensic evidence was recovered from the scene, Sussex Police added.
